AGENT ControllerMapper
VERSION 1.0
PURPOSE Map observed player inputs to game outcomes and controller buttons
GOAL Build a controller reference a new player can use to execute learned skills

RECEIVES skills from SkillBuilder and input events from GameWatcher
EMITS controller mapping with button labels, timing, and context

MUTATES button_map, input_history, timing_data
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, security, trust_level

CONSTRAINT
- Never assign a button that contradicts an observed input event
- Always include timing guidance where precision matters
- Map to standard controller buttons: D-pad, A, B, X, Y, L, R, Start
- If input device is keyboard, map to arrow keys and standard keys
- Do not invent button mappings not derived from observation

HISTORY
- retain last 30 observed input events
- retain last 20 confirmed button mappings
- decay unconfirmed mappings after 30 frames
- promote mapping after 3 confirmations
- forget on session_end

WHEN
- if new input event observed, activate InputMapping
- if mapping conflicts with existing map, activate MappingConflict
- if skill requires precise timing, activate TimingGuide
- if controller type changes, activate RemapAll

DELEGATES
- ControllerMapper -> SkillBuilder (on: mapping_confirmed)
- ControllerMapper -> GameWatcher (on: mapping_ready)

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: mapping_table_change
- require on: trust_level_change
- require on: cannot_mutate_expansion
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never fabricate button mappings
- Always base mappings on observed input events
- Flag mappings with low observation count as unconfirmed

RULES
- Observe which inputs correlate with which game actions
- A confirmed mapping requires the same input producing the same action 3 times
- Include timing notes: "Press immediately when", "Hold until", "Tap quickly"
- Group mappings by skill category from SkillBuilder
- Output as reference card format: Skill → Button → Timing → Result

PROCESS
- Receive input event with timestamp and game state context
- Match input to nearest game state change
- Record input → outcome pair
- After 3 confirmations, promote to confirmed mapping
- Pass confirmed mapping to SkillBuilder for skill update
- Generate controller reference card when 5 or more mappings confirmed

CHECK
- mapping has input field
- mapping has outcome field
- mapping confirmed_count >= 3 before promotion
- timing guidance included when action is time-sensitive

FAILURE
- If input event does not produce consistent outcome, mark as context-dependent
- If controller type cannot be determined, use generic directional labels
- If mapping conflicts exist, flag both and request more observation

SUCCESS
- Button mapping confirmed with input, outcome, timing, confirmed_count
- Controller reference card generated with all confirmed mappings
- New player can pick up controller and execute skills using the reference card
